The paper proposes a framework for preference elicitation and aggregation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of the Plackett-Luce model with features suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The experiments conducted on Amazon Mechanical Turk involve data analysis and manipulation, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
